{"id":2598,"date":"2022-01-29T20:54:52","date_gmt":"2022-01-29T20:54:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/?p=2598"},"modified":"2022-04-20T08:43:55","modified_gmt":"2022-04-20T08:43:55","slug":"fundamentals-of-html5","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/fundamentals-of-html5\/","title":{"rendered":"Fundamentals of HTML5 and CSS3"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Hypertext markup language (HTML) structures documents such as web pages by formatting the content available on the web pages and converting pure information into a graphically descriptive representation (Robbins, 2014). HTML was developed to a significant degree by Tim Berners-Lee (Walter, 2008) at the European Nuclear Research Center CERN in Geneva (European Organization for Nuclear Research, n.d.). HTML can be described as the language that ultimately gives web pages (and websites) the appearance and structure that is seen by end users.<\/p>\n<p>HTML\u2019s origin can be traced back to the development of the World Wide Web in the late 1990s (selfHTML, n.d.-b). One of the main goals of HTML was to create a description language that could run on any platform. At CERN, a way to efficiently distribute measurement data and research results was sought, so that, for example, the measurement data collected in Geneva could be analyzed by scientific institutions all over the world. For this, it was necessary to provide the raw data and a classical transmission protocol for adequate interpretation of the obtained results. This led to the birth of the internet, which resulted in the first version of the HTML specification on November 3, 1992 (selfHTML, n.d.-b).<\/p>\n<p>HTML differs from the programming languages discussed so far in that it knows no logical command flow structures (such as loops), but describes how the result (the web page) should ultimately look. To describe the respective commands, we work in tags, which begin in each case, for example, with a tag in the form<strong> &lt;h1&gt;<\/strong> and end with a tag in the form <strong>&lt;\/h1&gt;<\/strong>. This syntax is very similar to the syntax used in XML. For example, an HTML document is always introduced as follows:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">\r\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;head&gt;\r\n&lt;title&gt; Test Website &lt;\/title&gt;\r\n&lt;\/head&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h1&gt; Hello world &lt;\/h1&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;This is my first HTML document &lt;\/p&gt;\r\n&lt;a href=&quot;http:\/\/www.google.com\/&quot;&gt;I am a link&lt;\/a&gt;\r\n&lt;img src=&quot;Image.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;I am an image in an HTML document&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;\/body&gt;\r\n&lt;\/html&gt;<\/pre>\n<p>An HTML document always begins by declaring the document type. This ultimately serves to tell the browser what the document in question is about. This is an example of an HTML document, so the declaration can look like this: <strong>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<\/strong>. Then, the actual HTML elements follow. An HTML element always begins with a start tag in the form<strong> &lt;&#8230;&gt;,<\/strong> followed by the content of the respective tag and an end tag in the form <strong>&lt;\/&#8230;&gt;<\/strong>. In addition, an HTML document can have a header element, in which, for example, the title of a web page is defined. This will be displayed in the browser or the tab label of the browser. The actual content of an HTML document is listed in a body element.<\/p>\n<p>For example, <strong>&lt;h1&gt;<\/strong> is used to create a bold heading, after which <strong>&lt;p<\/strong>&gt; is used to introduce a paragraph. An <strong>&lt;a href&gt;<\/strong> tag leads to the definition of a link (the tag here is actually just \u201ca\u201d, \u201chref\u201d is, strictly speaking, an attribute that describes the characteristics of the \u201ca\u201d tag: here, around the exact link). An &lt;img&gt; tag is used to embed an image into the HTML web page. The modern advancement of HTML to HTML5 has also enabled targeted animation control, the embedding of videos, and much more. If web pages need to be extended by logical structures and arithmetic operations, or, for example, database connections are desired, this cannot be realized with HTML alone and requires the use of PHP. The HTML tags<strong> &lt;a&gt;&#8230;&lt;\/a&gt;<\/strong>, i.e., opening and closing tags, are also called HTML elements. Selected HTML tags, along with their functions, can be seen in the following table (selfHTML n.d.-b).<\/p>\n<table data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<colgroup data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<col style=\"width: 49.995%;\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\" \/>\n<col style=\"width: 50.01%;\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\" \/><\/colgroup>\n<thead data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<th colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Overview of Selected HTML Commands<\/span><\/span><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Command\/tag<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Description<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"> &lt;h1&gt; <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Headline (highest level)<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"> &lt;a href=\u201cURL\u201d&gt; <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Link<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"> &lt;img src=\u201cpath\u201d&gt; <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Embeds an image<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"> &lt;head&gt; <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Metadata<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"> &lt;title&gt; <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Website title<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"> &lt;table&gt; <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Table<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Attributes of HTML Tags<\/h2>\n<p>As mentioned above, attributes in HTML tags describe a more precise function. Through this, it is possible to assign further values to an HTML tag. Attributes are assigned within the tag, starting with the respective attribute and followed by the respective value of the attribute (separated by \u201c=\u201d), which is typically specified in quotation marks.<\/p>\n<p><strong>&lt;img&gt; element<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>With an <strong>&lt;img&gt;<\/strong> tag, it is possible to embed an image into an HTML web page: <strong>&lt;img src=&#8221;photo.png&#8221;&gt;<\/strong>. \u201cimg\u201d is an HTML element for controlling or including images in an HTML web page. With the \u201csrc\u201d attribute, it is possible to define the exact image (via the exact file name and, if applicable, the address path to the respective file, whereby both local addresses and addresses on the internet can be considered here). If we want to define the size of the image to be loaded, we can use the additional attributes \u201cwidth\u201d and \u201cheight\u201d: <strong>&lt;img src=&#8221;photo.png&#8221; width=&#8221;500&#8243; height=&#8221;600&gt;<\/strong>. In this case, the image to be loaded, \u201cphoto.png,\u201d would be displayed with a width of 500 x 600 pixels. If an image cannot be displayed, it is often helpful to offer a user a text that roughly reflects what the image is supposed to represent. One way we can achieve this is by using an \u201calt\u201d attribute. For example, if we want our website visitors to see the text \u201cIU Logo\u201d in case the image \u201cphoto.png\u201d cannot be loaded, we ensure the alternative output of the text using <strong>&lt;img src=&#8221;photo.png&#8221; alt=&#8221;Logo&#8221;&gt;<\/strong>. Some selected attributes of the &lt;img&gt; tag are shown in the following table.<\/p>\n<table data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<colgroup data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<col style=\"width: 13.985%;\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\" \/>\n<col style=\"width: 86.02%;\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\" \/><\/colgroup>\n<thead data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<th colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Selected Attributes of the <span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\">&lt;img&gt;<\/span><\/span> Tag<\/span><\/span><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Attribute<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Description<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\">src<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Path to image element<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\">old<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Text that is displayed when the desired image cannot be loaded.<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\">width<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Width of the image to be implemented<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr data-v-0ab77a18=\"\">\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"code-inline\" data-v-57cbfd26=\"\"><span data-v-57cbfd26=\"\">height<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<td class=\"\" colspan=\"\" rowspan=\"\" data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span data-v-0ab77a18=\"\"><span class=\"p\">Height of the image to be implemented<\/span><\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h3>Headings<\/h3>\n<p>To make a web page, especially a text, appear structured and clear, we can use headings. HTML has, like most word processing programs, different hierarchy levels for headings. The h1 tag is used to create the first hierarchy level of a heading. A heading lower in the hierarchy is then introduced by means of an h2 tag. Let\u2019s look at the following example to illustrate this:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h1&gt;Header 1&lt;\/h1&gt;\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr, sed diam nonumy\r\neirmod tempor invidunt ut labore et dolore magna aliquyam erat, sed diam\r\nvoluptua. At\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Header 2&lt;\/h2&gt;\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr, sed diam nonumy\r\neirmod tempor invidunt ut labore et dolore magna aliquyam erat, sed diam\r\nvoluptua. At\r\n&lt;h3&gt;Header 3&lt;\/h3&gt;\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr, sed diam nonumy\r\neirmod tempor invidunt ut labore et dolore magna aliquyam erat, sed diam\r\nvoluptua. At\r\n&lt;h4&gt;Header 4&lt;\/h4&gt;\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr, sed diam nonumy\r\neirmod tempor invidunt ut labore et dolore magna aliquyam erat, sed diam\r\nvoluptua. At\r\n&lt;h5&gt;Header 5&lt;\/h5&gt;\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr, sed diam nonumy\r\neirmod tempor invidunt ut labore et dolore magna aliquyam erat, sed diam\r\nvoluptua. At\r\n&lt;h6&gt;Header 6&lt;\/h6&gt;\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr, sed diam nonumy\r\neirmod tempor invidunt ut labore et dolore magna aliquyam erat, sed diam\r\nvoluptua. At\r\n&lt;\/body&gt;\r\n&lt;\/html&gt;\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>This results in the following output on the user\u2019s screen.<\/p>\n<h3><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2602\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1332\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1-350x311.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1-700x622.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1-768x682.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_5a951060119290eed8fd88b591ffbdd860f6596750a2739f9b53114ec29c6189-1-120x107.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><br \/>\nLorem Ipsum<\/h3>\n<p>The example text used here (\u201cLorem ipsum&#8230;\u201d) is a computer-generated filler text, which is often used as a placeholder in web design to give the external appearance a structure. This text is later replaced. This allows developers and designers to work on a project in parallel. \u201cLorem ipsum\u201d appears to be written in Latin, but has no semantic or syntactic meaning.<\/p>\n<h3>Comments<\/h3>\n<p>Often, when writing an HTML document, it can be useful (or even necessary) to leave comments in the document, e.g., as a note to oneself or a colleague regarding how something was implemented and why. This is achieved in HTML as follows: <strong>&lt;!- &#8211; I am a comment &#8211; &#8211; &gt;<\/strong>. The character combination at the beginning of a comment is interpreted by a browser such that it does not display the text contained in the comment in the user\u2019s browser. This text remains in the source code, hidden from the user.<\/p>\n<h3>Paragraphs<\/h3>\n<p>HTML is also capable of inserting paragraphs. This is advantageous in that continuous text, which is formulated coherently but differs slightly in the subject matter, can be separated for better readability. We can start a new paragraph with a <strong>&lt;p&gt;<\/strong> element followed by the content of the paragraph. Once the paragraph is finished, the paragraph is closed with the <strong>&lt;p&gt;<\/strong> tag:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">&lt;p&gt; Here is a paragraph. &lt;\/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt; Here is another paragraph. &lt;\/p&gt;\r\n<\/pre>\n<h3>Links<\/h3>\n<p>A very common tool in web design is the use of links. Links ultimately serve to redirect a user, e.g., with a mouse click, from one page to another. Links are created in HTML using an <strong>&lt;a&gt;<\/strong> element followed by an <strong>\u201chref\u201d<\/strong> attribute:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">&lt;a href=&quot;https:\/\/www.google.com\/&quot;&gt;Google&lt;\/a&gt;<\/pre>\n<p>Here we encounter another challenge: we may not want the link to be displayed as the actual URL, as this would affect the readability of the web page, especially when dealing with very long URLs. Instead, we can close the angle brackets after the \u201chref\u201d attribute and specify the text with which the included link will be labeled. The link element is then closed with the <strong>&lt;\/a<\/strong>&gt; tag.<\/p>\n<h3>Lists<\/h3>\n<p>It is often necessary to enumerate individual elements and give them an external structure. One way to achieve this is using lists. HTML is capable of generating both unordered and ordered lists.<\/p>\n<p>We define an unordered list with a <strong>ul<\/strong> element. Elements (the respective \u201clist items\u201d) are input with the<strong> li<\/strong> tag. With the following short HTML implementation, we can create an unordered shopping list:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Shopping list&lt;\/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Coffee&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Water&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Milk&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Ice cream&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;\/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;\/body&gt;\r\n&lt;\/html&gt;\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>In the browser, this unordered list is then displayed as follows.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2603\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"626\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2-350x146.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2-700x292.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2-768x321.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d575e340f7b820431758f406b8cfbac6f0cd5c4689cda520dd4bb0bdf288b3f2-120x50.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>The unordered list shown here can be quite easily converted to an ordered (numbered) list in HTML by creating the list using an <strong>&lt;ol&gt;<\/strong> (\u201cordered list\u201d) tag instead:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Shopping list&lt;\/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;ol&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Coffee&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Water&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Milk&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Ice cream&lt;\/li&gt;\r\n&lt;\/ol&gt;\r\n&lt;\/body&gt;\r\n&lt;\/html&gt;\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>This then leads to the following output.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2604\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"626\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543-350x146.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543-700x292.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543-768x321.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ec349d2c1661d5885101f46bc51a338a1b5b6be5fe87c562a13dbdd63a7aa543-120x50.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Tables<\/h3>\n<p>It is also possible to insert tables in HTML, e.g., in order to make information clear and comprehensible. A table is defined in HTML with the<strong> &lt;table&gt;<\/strong> tag. The <strong>&lt;tr&gt;<\/strong> tag then specifies the individual rows of the table. The respective header, i.e., the column heading of a table, is created with the <strong>&lt;th&gt;<\/strong> tag. The respective entries (or table data) in a cell are embedded as <strong>&lt;td&gt;<\/strong> tags. An HTML table is structured in such a way that the description of the table ultimately becomes increasingly specific, i.e., from the table declaration itself to the content of a specific cell. The formatting HTML uses is already stored in the HTML standard, so entries in the <strong>&lt;th&gt;<\/strong> element will always appear bold and centered.<\/p>\n<p>In the following example, we will try to compile the stock of a small warehouse in a HTML table. The hypothetical inventory system should have options for entering an item description, an item number, the price, and the quantity available in the warehouse. Three articles (1\u20143) are then to be entered into the table as an example. A possible implementation of such a table is as follows:<\/p>\n<p>Code<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;h2&gt;stock&lt;\/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;table&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;\r\n&lt;th&gt;Item&lt;\/th&gt;\r\n&lt;th&gt;Itemno&lt;\/th&gt;\r\n&lt;th&gt;Price&lt;\/th&gt;\r\n&lt;th&gt;Quantity&lt;\/th&gt;\r\n&lt;\/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;Item 1&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;1234&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;50&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;94&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;\/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;Item2&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;4567&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;25&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;20&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;\/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;tr&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;Item 3&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;5794&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;10&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;td&gt;45&lt;\/td&gt;\r\n&lt;\/tr&gt;\r\n&lt;\/table&gt;\r\n&lt;\/body&gt;\r\n&lt;\/html&gt;\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>The corresponding output in the browser would look like this.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2605\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"490\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739-350x114.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739-700x229.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739-768x251.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d91dad1df1079bb0075fb31ef328901d5b402255f4b841261529ec57aa7e8739-120x39.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2>ID of an HTML Element<\/h2>\n<p>Similar to how a name identifies a person, we can also assign names to individual HTML elements in order to identify them again later. For example, if we have a heading that is described by an <strong>&lt;h1&gt;<\/strong> element, we can assign a name to it using the \u201cid\u201d attribute. In concrete terms, an implementation would look like this:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">&lt;h1 id=&quot;FirstHeader&quot;&gt;I am a header&lt;\/h1&gt;<\/pre>\n<p>The IDs of an HTML document are not displayed in the browser. They are only used for internal reference. The declaration of an ID for an HTML element is case sensitive. This means that even identical names will result in correspondingly different IDs once different upper- and lowercase letters are used.<\/p>\n<p>So, what are IDs useful for? With IDs, it becomes possible to access or refer to the element with the desired ID at (almost) any place in the HTML document (this is typically achieved by means of a pound sign (#) placed in front of the ID). For example, we can introduce a style element into the header of an HTML document, which is opened with <strong>&lt;style&gt;,<\/strong> followed by the respective content, and closed with <strong>&lt;\/style&gt;.<\/strong> For example, if we want to set the background color of the heading to blue, we would use the following code.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2606\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"794\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a-350x185.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a-700x371.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a-768x407.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_c9ea754e32161c8ecf67d0a1b2c5c6d384ac20236fd7f058da462723fa485e4a-120x64.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Here we have also used a style definition, which actually follows the syntax of Cascading Style Sheets (CSS). In the style element, the heading with the respective ID is addressed by \u201c#FirstHeading\u201d and applied to the commands that are listed in curly brackets that follow. In this case, this refers only to the background color, i.e., \u201cbackground-color,\u201d to which we assign the value \u201cblue.\u201d This is confirmed with a semicolon. In the user\u2019s browser, this would lead to the following output.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2607\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"359\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c-350x84.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c-700x168.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c-768x184.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_73e0202c9137b654929d5ebb9ace1c90ba72c1782dadbb0bd62188ab06c3399c-120x29.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2>Classes<\/h2>\n<p>In the same way IDs can be assigned to HTML elements, it is also possible to aggregate several HTML elements into a class. A class definition is introduced by the \u201cclass\u201d attribute. If this is accessed again in a later step, the same operation is applied to all class elements. While accessing IDs takes place by means of a pound sign, this is done for classes by means of a prefixed period (.). Let\u2019s look at an another example.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2608\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"984\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001-350x230.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001-700x459.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001-768x504.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_157f0e26c77b191ab3cfee9a14dc4754e9a95a6d62055d69c1f6dc9e2b3c4001-120x79.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>In this example document, we have embedded some headings that are assigned to the classes \u201cFirstHeading\u201d and \u201cSecondHeading.\u201d We have now specified a style definition for each of the two classes in the style element. All elements that belong to the class \u201cFirstHeading\u201d have a blue background. All elements of the class \u201cSecondHeading\u201d have a yellow background. This leads to the following output in the browser<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2609\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"696\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280-350x162.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280-700x325.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280-768x356.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_071c0c442d6688826ef844c066d54afe9e90f00cb405ecc13d8e59488e83f280-120x56.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>div class<\/h3>\n<p>A very commonly used class is the div class. By means of div elements, it is possible to group text, namely the text that is inserted inside the div element:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">&lt;div&gt; Here comes the text &lt;\/div&gt;<\/pre>\n<p>We will see below, especially in the context of CSS, that the use of such div classes offers some advantages when it comes to setting the design for an HTML document.<\/p>\n<h2>Creation of a Form Using HTML<\/h2>\n<p>Forms in web applications are typically still generated using HTML. A form can generally have the following form elements:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>single-line and multi-line text fields for input<\/li>\n<li>elements for file upload<\/li>\n<li>selection lists<\/li>\n<li>text fields by means of which the arrow keys can be used to increase or decrease the corresponding values<\/li>\n<li>radio buttons for either\/or selection<\/li>\n<li>checkboxes for both\/and selection<\/li>\n<li>dates<\/li>\n<li>buttons<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>For these elements, HTML has <strong>&lt;form&gt;<\/strong> tags, which allow the creation of forms, or, in essence, input fields. A form is placed between <strong>&lt;form&gt;<\/strong> and <strong>&lt;\/form&gt;.<\/strong> Everything that is entered inside this tag is recognized as form content when the HTML code is later processed by the browser. We can generate the first input field using the command below.<\/p>\n<form><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2610\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"316\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b-350x74.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b-700x147.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b-768x162.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_474d5011280a8ac4b4f9a807134ebf042befea0e09e67774fb48b9552b59380b-120x25.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>This has the heading \u201cFirst name.\u201d Using <strong>&lt;br&gt;<\/strong> moves us to the next line and we use the <strong>&lt;input&gt;<\/strong> tag to define what form and input line should accept. Using the \u201ctype\u201d attribute, we define a \u201ctext,\u201d i.e., an input line is created into which text can be entered. Using \u201cid,\u201d we can assign a unique identifier to the input text line. This will become important later, for example, when we want to collectively read the data from the form to forward it by e-mail or store it in a database. We can also assign a name to the input line. This is done using \u201cname.\u201d Here, we assign the name \u201cfname.\u201d Using \u201cvalue,\u201d we can define which default value should be present in the input field when the form is first called. This can help the end user or the customer know in which format an address, for example, should be entered. Ultimately, however, assigning \u201cid,\u201d \u201cname,\u201d and \u201cvalue\u201d is an optional step. We can now generate an entire form to record a customer\u2019s address. A possible implementation in HTML would look like the following figure.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2611\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1033\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b-350x241.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b-700x482.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b-768x529.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e6709b1086ed72719ac46699f4dacdf7dc98b658c193d0c2f4beb23d7f39108b-120x83.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Using the value attributes, the corresponding input cells are pre-filled with a default value. However, these can be changed by the user. Just as in the procedure already described, we now implement the individual form fields in the <strong>&lt;form&gt;<\/strong> tag, which can be found in the HTML body, and extend our previous line for entering the first name with a field for the last name, the address, the place of residence, and the postal code. As we would expected from an input form on the internet, a form ends with a \u201csubmit\u201d button, which is responsible for sending the form (submitting an order or a contact form). This is achieved in HTML by means of an input tag of the type \u201csubmit.\u201d Using the value option, it is possible to specify a label text for the button. In this example, we label it \u201cSubmit.\u201d In a browser, the form implemented in HTML above would appear as follows.<\/p>\n<\/form>\n<form><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2612\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"978\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e-350x228.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e-700x456.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e-768x501.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e898cb1470e34410d385b9897c1854b3937ca492cecc172763aebfca73d8af2e-120x78.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Admittedly, the form does not yet look particularly appealing. This form is a purely functional and technical implementation. We can visually polish the form further through the additional use of CSS stylesheets or even special JavaScript classes, but this is outside the scope of this introductory course.<\/p>\n<h3>Drop-down menus<\/h3>\n<p>Forms in HTML are not purely limited to the text input fields seen above. We can also create drop-down menus that, for example, allow a customer to select a specific color of the item they wish to purchase. A possible implementation for a drop-down color selection menu could look like this.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2614\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"631\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1-350x147.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1-700x294.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1-768x323.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_e499787c36c6f4563d776889f8201f346590a89dcc64a8a1479fb7d3958072af-1-120x50.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>We create a drop-down menu using <strong>&lt;select&gt;<\/strong> tags, where the individual options available for selection in the drop-down menu can then be specified. The value attribute is the value that is assigned to the selected field. For example, it is possible to assign a number when selecting the color blue, which can be useful if, for example, different colors of a t-shirt have different prices. For example, we can provide the selection option \u201cblue\u201d to the end user but use the price of the shirt internally for invoicing. If we look at the selection option for the color \u201cred,\u201d we notice the additional option \u201cselected.\u201d This is the value of the drop-down menu that is listed as the default when the form is called. In the browser, the above form would be displayed as follows:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2615\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"457\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd-350x107.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd-700x213.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd-768x234.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_d6a4760b7ca76cad2d5474955f9586745ad4e5b0c12ce6627193b4b74753b2dd-120x37.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>For the actual reading and sending of the form data, however, we need help from more advanced concepts, such as PHP.<\/p>\n<h2>Fundamentals of CSS3<\/h2>\n<p class=\"p\">CSS is the abbreviation for the term \u201ccascading style sheets\u201d and describes how HTML elements should be displayed (selfHTML, n.d.-a). CSS allows for a better, more formative conversion of information: A major advantage of defining the appearance of HTML pages using CSS is that the appearance of HTML elements only needs to be defined once. This can then be applied to the entire HTML document without the need to further redefine the appearance for each HTML element used.<\/p>\n<section class=\"section\" data-v-fbef277c=\"\">\n<div data-v-fbef277c=\"\">\n<h3 class=\"title\"><span data-v-57b57216=\"\">CSS Structure<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p\">CSS is always structured in the same way: a CSS rule consists of a\u00a0<span class=\"bold-text is-inline\" data-v-00cf571e=\"\"><span data-v-00cf571e=\"\"><span class=\"text-with-popup\" data-v-0f647a5f=\"\">selector<\/span><\/span><\/span>\u00a0and a\u00a0<span class=\"bold-text is-inline\" data-v-00cf571e=\"\"><span data-v-00cf571e=\"\"><span class=\"text-with-popup\" data-v-0f647a5f=\"\">declaration<\/span><\/span><\/span>. A selector is an element that specifies which HTML elements the declaration following the selector should refer to. The declaration then determines how the HTML element in question is to be formatted. The declaration can be made either in a separate CSS file, which can be stored together with the HTML document on a server, or stored in the style element directly in the HTML document. The interaction between HTML, CSS, and other media is described in the following figure.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2634\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1380\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1-350x322.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1-700x644.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1-768x707.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_097b55cb584185f0053db3c1fd66f055e7c1b51d9e652cce0038b037935ac149-1-120x110.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Content is inserted into an HTML document, the subsequent presentation of which can be described using HTML. The exact formatting of the respective descriptive HTML tags is determined by a CSS, which interacts with the HTML document and is ultimately aggregated to the final web page. Based on the HTML document, further functionality can be added to the web page by integrating additional scripts (e.g., JavaScript). The integration of media (e.g., images) is also possible.<\/p>\n<p>Let\u2019s look at this again using an example in which we want to have all HTML elements declared as &lt;p&gt; elements left-aligned and displayed in blue. The CSS description required for this would be as follows.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2635\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"870\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7-350x203.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7-700x406.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7-768x445.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_159a4f87c3c7ec86462d2da69e1881d48bb0b5b58785fff2bccbd54ef3e048b7-120x70.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>As already mentioned, the CSS description in the style element takes place directly in the HTML document. If a &lt;p&gt; element is then defined in the further course of the HTML document, it is displayed according to the CSS description. The following output would appear on the user\u2019s screen.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2636\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"381\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a-350x89.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a-700x178.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a-768x195.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_ba056fa788b45663773ee429c215fb3b35c441ea09be4d7f5f7c5ac1704c345a-120x30.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Comments<\/h3>\n<p>For better clarity and comprehensibility, it is also possible to store comments in CSS. A comment can be introduced by \u201c\/*,\u201d followed by the actual comment text, and closed again with \u201c*\/.\u201d For example, we can introduce a comment as follows:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\" title=\"\">\/* I am a comment *\/<\/pre>\n<h3>Background Color<\/h3>\n<p>In CSS, it is not only possible to change the font color, but also to set the background color of a web page or HTML element. Using the CSS command \u201cbackground-color,\u201d it is possible to change the background color of a web page. Again, as explained above, the structure of the CSS statement is identical (built from selector and declaration). Using the following command, the background color of the \u201cbody\u201d area is set to blue.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2637\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"446\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3-350x104.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3-700x208.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3-768x228.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_a12f460587d2f124add8c9569ea618b87b16d0aa82394c61c45702b440893cd3-120x36.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>The body area is generally understood to be the background of a web page.<\/p>\n<h3>Margins<\/h3>\n<p>Using margins, it is possible to define an HTML element\u2019s distance from the edge of the screen or browser window. Let\u2019s look at this again with an example.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2638\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1272\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae-350x297.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae-700x594.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae-768x651.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_66a2d318d47f6a78b11b32cca5ead8020c19a8aa26019bb8aba6dbed715ea6ae-120x102.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>For the div element, we use the margin commands to define the respective margins, e.g., margin-left defines the left margin in pixels. Using border, it is possible to draw a frame around the respective HTML element. In this example, the border should be 2 pixels wide, solid, and black. The background color for the div element is set to yellow in this example.<\/p>\n<p>For the heading h2 we want it to be blue in color and flush (relative to the left side) with the div element.<\/p>\n<p>The body element is followed by the implementations of the h2 element and the div element.<\/p>\n<p>This results in the following output on the user or developer\u2019s screen.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2639\" src=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"381\" srcset=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed.jpg 1500w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed-350x89.jpg 350w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed-700x178.jpg 700w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed-768x195.jpg 768w, https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/relative_9ccb5c372c5efa4aca74be67c6941da2a3a6c4ac45fc55592c7f26463f5094ed-120x30.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div data-v-fbef277c=\"\">\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>\n<\/form>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Hypertext markup language (HTML) structures documents such as web pages by formatting the content available on the web pages and converting pure information into a graphically descriptive representation (Robbins, 2014). HTML was developed to a significant degree by Tim Berners-Lee (Walter, 2008) at the European Nuclear Research Center CERN in Geneva (European Organization for Nuclear [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":2630,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[62,55],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v18.0 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Fundamentals of HTML5 and CSS3 | Web Development | JJ<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/fundamentals-of-html5\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Fundamentals of HTML5 and CSS3 | Web Development | JJ\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Hypertext markup language (HTML) structures documents such as web pages by formatting the content available on the web pages and converting pure information into a graphically descriptive representation (Robbins, 2014). HTML was developed to a significant degree by Tim Berners-Lee (Walter, 2008) at the European Nuclear Research Center CERN in Geneva (European Organization for Nuclear [&hellip;]\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/jacekjeznach.com\/fundamentals-of-html5\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" 